# Technical Writing Portfolio

Welcome to my technical writing portfolio.

## About me
I am a Principal Technical Content Developer with over 15 years of experience creating and transforming technical documentation for global technology leaders including Dell Technologies and IBM. 
My expertise spans software documentation, API documentation, UX writing, content strategy, information architecture, and content operations.

Throughout my career, I have led large-scale documentation initiatives that modernized content ecosystems, improved documentation quality, and enhanced content delivery efficiency. I specialize in developing scalable content strategies, implementing governance frameworks, and driving documentation standardization across complex product portfolios.
At Dell Technologies, I have spearheaded cross-functional initiatives focused on API documentation, AI-enabled content development, UX writing, and content engineering. My work has consistently delivered measurable improvements in productivity, content reuse, and operational efficiency while maintaining a 100% on-time delivery record.

I am particularly passionate about the future of technical communication and the application of AI within content development. My recent work includes leading AI curriculum development for global content teams, 
researching LLM-assisted content review processes, and exploring knowledge graph frameworks for intelligent content delivery.

In addition to industry leadership, I actively contribute to the advancement of the profession through lecturing on the Master's programme in Technical Communication and E-Learning at the University of Limerick.

